cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper discusses the application of deep neural networks to energy disaggregation, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of recurrent neural networks, denoising autoencoders, and regression networks, which are all subfields of deep learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with time series data, which falls under the sub-category cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of energy consumption, which is a problem in control systems, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the generalization of the neural net algorithms to an unseen house, which is a problem in systems and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible sub-category.
